This is the README file for this package.


Installation
============

Unpack the distribution tarball:

$ tar xzf serveez-<version>.tar.gz                  (using GNU tar)
$ gzip -cd ../serveez-<version>.tar.gz | tar xf -   (using another tar)
  
Change into the source directory:

$ cd serveez-<version>   
  
Configure the source package for your system.
We recommend to use --enable-opt unless you have a good reason not to do so.

$ ./configure --enable-opt

Compile the package recursively.

$ make
  
Install serveez.

$ make install

You must change to root privileges, if you want to install the
package in the standard location /usr/local or in any location that is
only writable by root.

For further information on installing the package, please consult the
file INSTALL, included in this distribution.


Getting the latest CVS snapshot
===============================

cvs -d :pserver:anoncvs@lkcc.pinuts.de:/home/cvs/cvsroot -z 9 co serveez

you probably need to run
$ sh autogen.sh
